description.narrative: Cross-sectoral approaches: Strategies to address cross-cutting issues related to child rights are developed and applied., which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Supply And Logistics, Unicef Capacity For Supply And Logistics. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Capacities of subnational institutions are enhanced for child-sensitive and participatory social policy planning to support vulnerable girls and boys.
